The separator is placed inside each `StepperItem` (after the trigger/title). The last step should NOT include a separator -- this is the consumer's responsibility. This follows the BreadcrumbSeparator pattern where the separator is an explicit, manually placed element.

**F. The separator colors based on its parent StepperItem's state:**
When a StepperItem is `"completed"`, its separator turns primary-colored, showing visual progress. When active or upcoming, it stays muted. This means the separator between step 1 and step 2 is colored when step 1 is completed (i.e., when the user is on step 2 or beyond).

